# Frontend Development Rules

## Next.js Patterns

- Use server components by default
- Only use `'use client'` for Web API access
- Use App Router with proper loading/error boundaries

## Component Architecture

- Use functional components with TypeScript types
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use descriptive variable names (isLoading, hasError)

## State Management

- Use 'nuqs' for URL search parameter state
- Minimize useState and useEffect
- Prefer server state over client state

## Performance & UI

- Wrap client components in Suspense
- Use TailwindCSS for styling
- Use Shadcn/UI for components
